body.p:
To solve this issue, you can use Segoe UI as a fallback font.
      In your customization CSS,
      add:*[class ~= "topic/dl"] {
  font-family: "Roboto", "Segoe UI";
}

To change the font for the entire publication, not just an element, you can
      use::root {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }

@page {
    @top-left {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @top-right {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @top-center {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @top-left-corner {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @top-right-corner {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }

    @bottom-left {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @bottom-right {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @bottom-center {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @bottom-left-corner {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
    @bottom-right-corner {font-family:  "Roboto", "Segoe UI" !important; }
}
